Iu Lucr. contra, ante, post, super, supera (serora), and subter are oftener adverbs than prepositions. circum, extra, inter, praeter, propter are also frequently adverbs. Holtze, ‘Syutaxis Lucretianae Lineamenta’ cap. 4, gives abundant illustrations of the different uses. 68. fama: Bentley, whom Lachmann follows, reads sana instead of sama ; be· cause, as Lachmann says, scilicet sama non omnis necessario m agna est. Fama not only has the authority of the MSS, but also gives better sense; for it was not so much the existence of gods or shrines of the gods as the unfounded story of them, that inspired fear.
